Package: bouquets
Title: Angular Accumulation Plots for Time Series
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R:
    person("Max", "Nölscher", , "max-n@posteo.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5606-1900"))
Description: Creates angular accumulation ("bouquet") plots for collections
    of time series. Each series is encoded as a sequence of signed directional
    steps and drawn as a turtle-graphics path that turns left on increases and
    right on decreases. All series share a common origin and angle, so visual
    pattern similarity directly reflects similarity in directional dynamics.
    Companion functions cluster series by directional similarity (with S3
    summary and quality-plot helpers), highlight individual series, filter by
    time window, normalise per-series angles, and optionally attach a
    geographic location map with cluster hull overlays. An interactive plotly
    version with hover tooltips is also provided.
